{{Infobox journal | editor = Enzo Rossi, Matt Sleat | cover = Ejpt.gif | title = European Journal of Political Theory | discipline = [[Political philosophy|Political theory and philosophy]] | abbreviation = Eur. J. Political Theory | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2002–present | impact = 0.437 | impact-year = 2014 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal201560/title | link1 = http://ept.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://ept.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1474-8851 | eISSN = 1741-2730 | OCLC = 300290660 | LCCN = 2003203027 }} The '''''European Journal of Political Theory''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers the field of [[Political philosophy|political theory and philosophy]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Enzo Rossi ([[University of Amsterdam]]) and Matt Sleat ([[University of Sheffield]]). It was established 2002 and is published by [[Sage Publications]].
